  {"id": "seg_00158", "translation": "From this we conclude that −2 and 2 are relative minima, and 0 is a relative maximum. The corresponding function values are:"},
  {"id": "seg_00159", "translation": ","},
  {"id": "seg_00160", "translation": "."},
  {"id": "seg_00161", "translation": "Careful examination shows that the function "},
  {"id": "seg_00162", "translation": " has no absolute maximum but does have an absolute minimum. In this problem, the relative minimum also happens to be the absolute minimum. More generally, every degree-4 polynomial has no absolute maximum but always has an absolute minimum — except, of course, on a closed interval."},
  {"id": "seg_00163", "translation": "The graph of this function is shown below:"},
